quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  112,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬHe is GodвАФOne Ћєand IndivisibleЋЇ"
  112,2,GodвАФthe Sustainer Ћєneeded by allЋЇ
  112,3,"He has never had offspring, nor was He born"
  112,4,And there is none comparable to Him.вАЭ
  113,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of whatever He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the night when it grows dark
  113,4,and from the evil of those Ћєwitches casting spells byЋЇ blowing onto knots
  113,5,and from the evil of an envier when they envy.вАЭ
  114,1,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬI seek refuge in the Lord of humankind"
  114,2,the Master of humankind
  114,3,the God of humankind
  114,4,from the evil of the lurking whispererвАФ
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of humankindвАФ
  114,6,from among jinn and humankind.вАЭ
